<paragraph blockId="10.[718,1267,384,569]" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis box="[718,902,384,408]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Remarks – Liornis</emphasis>
Ameghino,1895, with the species 
<taxonomicName authority="Ameghino, 1895" authorityName="Ameghino" authorityYear="1895" box="[718,984,416,440]" class="Aves" family="Aves (awaiting allocation)" genus="Lophiornis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aves (awaiting allocation)" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="floweri">
<emphasis box="[718,803,416,440]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">L. floweri</emphasis>
Ameghino, 1895
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Dolgopol de Saez, 1927" authorityName="Dolgopol de Saez" authorityYear="1927" class="Aves" family="Phororhacidae" genus="Ameghinornis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gruiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis box="[1045,1125,417,440]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">L. minor</emphasis>
Dolgopol de Saez, 1927
</taxonomicName>
, are evident synonyms of 
<taxonomicName authority="Ameghino, 1887" authorityName="Ameghino" authorityYear="1887" class="Aves" family="Phorusrhacidae" genus="Phorusrhacos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gruiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1143,1266,448,472]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Phorusrhacos</emphasis>
Ameghino, 1887
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Kraglievich 1932" authorityName="Kraglievich" authorityYear="1932" box="[894,1178,480,504]" class="Aves" family="Phorusrhacidae" genus="Devincenzia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gruiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[894,1001,481,504]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Devincenzia</emphasis>
Kraglievich 1932
</taxonomicName>
, is surely a robust form of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ameghino" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[884,1039,512,536]" class="Aves" family="Phorusrhacidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gruiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Phorusrhacinae">Phorusrhacinae</taxonomicName>
. These two genera were dealt with as synonyms of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moreno &amp; Mercerat" authorityYear="1891" box="[974,1065,545,568]" class="Aves" family="Brontornithidae" genus="Brontornis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gruiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[974,1065,545,568]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Brontornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Brodkorb (1967).
</paragraph>
